              <h3>Two U of M Alumni Named among Forbes 30 Under 30</h3> 
              <p class="date"><span class="date-display-single">January 13, 2015</span></p> 
              <img class="image-scaled-3x2-648x432" src="http://twin-cities.umn.edu/sites/twin-cities.umn.edu/files/styles/image_scaled_3x2_648x432/public/carlson-school-alumni.jpg?itok=bpmnb-Oh" width="648" height="432" alt="Asha Sharma headshot in front of a multi color geographic background."> 
              <div class="article-content"> 
               <p>Two University of Minnesota alumni have earned coveted positions on the 2015 <i>Forbes</i> 30 Under 30 list, an honor that celebrates 600 young people across 20 fields who are changing the face of tomorrow.&nbsp; </p>
               <p>U of M Carlson School of Management graduates Asha Sharma, ‘11 and Erik Eliason, ‘08 share the honor with other “game changers” ranging from NBA basketball player James Harden and actor Keira Knightley to Glossier founder Emily Weiss and Alan Schaaf, founder of Imgur.</p>
